3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses a new research direction that sheds light on interesting problems at the intersection of computational complexity and group theory. This suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures, which fall under the cs.DS sub-category.
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper discusses the complexity of computing almost unitary matrices, which may involve geometric considerations. This suggests a connection to computational geometry, which falls under the cs.CG sub-category.
5. cs.GR (Graphics): Although less likely than the other sub-categories, the paper's focus on computing matrices with the Fourier transform may have applications in graphics, such as image processing. This suggests a connection to graphics, which falls under the cs.GR sub-category.
